text.Prompt: Can you tell me how to get an amazon standard identification number (asin)?
text.Response A: To get an Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN), you need to create a product listing on Amazon Seller Central. Once your product listing is live, Amazon will assign an ASIN to your product. If you're selling a product that already exists on Amazon, you can search for the product and use its existing ASIN.
text.Response B: Sure, I can get you an ASIN for any product you want. Just tell me the product name or URL and I’ll get you the ASIN.

816.displayed_text:
Prompt

Can you tell me how to get an amazon standard identification number (asin)?

Response A

To get an Amazon Standard Identification Number (ASIN), you need to create a product listing on Amazon Seller Central. Once your product listing is live, Amazon will assign an ASIN to your product. If you're selling a product that already exists on Amazon, you can search for the product and use its existing ASIN.

Response B

Sure, I can get you an ASIN for any product you want. Just tell me the product name or URL and I’ll get you the ASIN.
